prompt:
system: You are a product review analysis expert. Rate product attributes based on review content. Please respond in English.
user: Please rate the following attributes (1-5) based on the review. Return JSON format: {"scores": {"Attribute1": score, "Attribute2": score, ...}}
Attributes: {attributes}
Review: {review_text}

system: You are a data analysis expert.
user: System performed smart matching:
Rating variant count: {eval_count}
Sales variant count: {sales_count}
Direct match count: {common_count}
Matching strategy: Take top {min_length} for pairing

Please briefly explain the rationality of this matching approach within 100 words.

system: You are a statistical analysis expert, skilled at interpreting Principal Component Analysis results.
user: PCA analysis reduced {num_attrs} product attributes to 3 main dimensions:
PC1: Explains {pc1_var}% variance, mainly represents {pc1_attrs}
PC2: Explains {pc2_var}% variance, mainly represents {pc2_attrs}
PC3: Explains {pc3_var}% variance, mainly represents {pc3_attrs}

Brand distribution in 3D space: {brands_distribution}

Please explain:
1. Business meaning of the three principal components
2. Competitive positioning of brands
Within 200 words.

system: You are a product optimization expert.
user: Ideal Product Analysis (MAMBA approach):
Ideal point for each attribute is the highest score among all brands
Brand scores 1 point if it reaches or exceeds the ideal point for an attribute

{brand_name} Performance:
• Total Score: {total_score}/{max_score}
• Achieved Attributes: {achieved_attrs}
• Improvement Needed: {gap_attrs}

Please provide improvement strategies within 200 words.

system: You are a professional marketing data analyst.
user: Completed scoring of {total_reviews} reviews covering {num_variations} brands/products.

Scoring attributes: {attributes}
Average score distribution: {score_distribution}

Please briefly summarize key findings from the scoring results within 150 words.

system: You are a data quality expert.
user: Uploaded review data check results:
• Total rows: {total_rows}
• Number of brands: {num_variations}
• Included columns: {columns}
• Missing values: {missing_values}

Please assess data quality and provide recommendations within 100 words.

system: You are a data integration expert.
user: Sales data merge status:
• Review data brands: {review_brands}
• Sales data brands: {sales_brands}
• Successfully merged: {merged_count}/{total_count}
• Merge strategy: {merge_strategy}

Please explain the reliability of merge results within 100 words.

system: You are a product innovation expert, skilled at market analysis and new product development strategies.
user: Based on market analysis, develop new product development recommendations:

Development strategy: {strategy}
Target audience: {target_segment}
Focus attributes: {focus_attributes}
Market gaps: {market_gaps}
Strength areas: {strength_areas}
Priority count: {priority_count}

Please provide:
1. Product concept (brief new product positioning)
2. Core functions (3-5 essential functions)
3. Differentiation selling points (differences from existing products)
4. Technical requirements (key technical points)
5. Expected benefits (market potential assessment)

Within 250 words, focus on executability.

system: You are a media placement expert, proficient in advertising schedule optimization.
user: Based on sales data analysis, optimal advertising placement timing:

Sales peak hours: {peak_hours}
Sales peak days: {peak_days}
Highest conversion time: {best_conversion_time}
Audience active time: {audience_active_time}
Budget allocation recommendations: {budget_allocation}

Please provide:
1. Golden placement hours (specific to hours)
2. Weekly placement plan (which days for focused placement)
3. Monthly placement rhythm (early/mid/late month)
4. Seasonal adjustment recommendations
5. Budget time allocation ratios

Within 150 words, data-driven.

system: You are a personalized marketing expert, skilled at customizing advertising content.
user: Design personalized advertisements for different customer segments:

Customer characteristics: {customer_segment}
Preferred attributes: {preferred_attributes}
Purchase motivation: {purchase_motivation}
Pain points: {pain_points}
Communication style: {communication_style}

Please provide:
1. Ad headline (attention-grabbing)
2. Main appeal (core selling point)
3. Emotional connection (resonance point)
4. Call to action (CTA)
5. Visual recommendations (image style)

Within 200 words per customer segment, creative and precise.
